Hey, everyone! 👋

There’s lots of new followers here in the new year, so I thought I’d do a quick reintroduction of myself. There really is a person behind this page!

I’m Lisa—a wife, mom & caffeine addict. ☕️ I live in Northern California with my husband & 4 boys. Well, I say boys but most of my sons are young men now. I started this page 7 years ago, when my kids were giving me endless material that I regularly made into funny tweets/memes. Every day was full of “you can’t make this shit up!” moments. Parenthood is no easy task, so why not try to laugh about it? Turns out a lot of you agreed! 

I’ve always wanted this page to be a place where parents can come to get a laugh & find many relatable moments so they know they’re not alone on their parenting journey. I get so many messages saying “OMG I thought I was the only one!” or “I’m so glad this is a normal way to feel about xyz.” 

I just want to thank you all for being here & helping me grow this supportive community. I appreciate all of your comments & messages. Some of your comments are hilarious & you make ME laugh! And believe me, there are many days I need that. So please stick around, tell a friend. There’s many more laughs to come! ♥️
Nobody likes a whiner but parents get a free pass! (@josh.dad.gillett)
Heck, just put the kids to bed & give me 🍷! (@mommywinetime)

Parenthood can seem like the most thankless job but then this happened. 

My son went with me to the grocery store yesterday to get Super Bowl snacks. He disappeared, like he always does. I assumed he was off looking for a drink. When he met back up with me, he was holding this little bouquet of flowers for me. Bought with his own money. I was shocked! And totally embarrassed him by hugging him in the middle of the packed grocery store! 

They are worth every hour of sleep I have lost & every dime I have spent. All I can ask is that my kids grow up to be decent humans. I think they’re doing just fine. ♥️
